Dettaaaiilllsssss!!!!!!!! @stoneyclover are the Queeeeens of detail…our gingerbread install number2 was no exception….down to the pieces of glitter and pearls! 🤌🏻👍🏻 also the gumdrops that @amriels_cakes made!!! We assumed the transition from baker to gumdrop maker would be a smooth transition 😂👍🏻 except we greatly underestimated how looooong these guys would take🫣 …mixing plaster and hours and hours of whittling and shaping said plaster and styrofoam…her arms were sore for a week 😂😂😂😂😂😂💪🏼 I mean…worth it though! 👌🏻I am wondering if I could coerce her into making me some in CA now 🙋🏻‍♀️🤪 Amriels Cakes and Gumdrops…coming soon! 😜😅
Also, we are in the last few days of our work year!!! 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 Praying we knock it out and then take time to rest and recoup 💗💗💗 we feel so Blessed to have had the opportunities we’ve had!  But also I haven’t boxed up all my Halloween decor entirely 😂😂😜😵‍💫😂 balance! 10/10!

It’s raining here in CA….which means it’s snowing just up the mountain…which means the Rogers Big Bear getaway will be a snow-filled adventure this weekend!!! The kids intend to ski or snowboard or something strenuous….I intend to find a chalet just like this and sit there and sip something warm while I await their arrival…prayerfully with all their bones intact 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 So…this was our last event of 2022…an eggnog gathering with an apres ski twist!  Complete with custom bar, ski lift, foosball, giant bear, singing reindeer …all the things to transport you from a patio in Beverly Hills to a lodge in Vermont maybe!? 🤷🏻‍♀️😂😂😂🤌🏻 thank you for having us @lanagomez !!!!! One day I will need to try eggnog!! 👌🏻😂

What’s it like to build not one, not two, but THREE gingerbread houses in one month’s time!? In Three different states??! 😂😂😂 From New York to Florida to California…we did a full @stoneyclover store front, a full build from scratch, and a convertible booth/ mini backdrop gingerbread house to round it up….each build had its own unique challenges…each location had its own character (the New York build I love because it’s this unexpected pastel land amongst the brown NY buildings)……my goodness, we will look back at this season with a grateful heart and a ton of memories…..and a record number of people asking us if we like glitter 😂😂😂😂 because literally we’ve been unintentionally covered in it for an entire month!!! 😜😜😜

The most insane work year made for the Most Random highlight reel 😂😂😂👌🏻🤌🏻!!!! I’m not even sure how this was all done in a year’s time 🤷🏻‍♀️🤷🏻‍♀️🤷🏻‍♀️😂😂 but my goodness….what a Blessing it has been to create so many memories with so many families!!! And…..getting to work with our favorite brands!!!!! And TRAVEL!?? Boy, did we travel!  The amount of bagged pretzels I ate in the sky this year! 🤯😂😂 Also, Erik Not catching a football on the Tampa Bay football field will be a Forever highlight for me!!! 💯Wishing you all a Happy, Healthy New Year!!! May God Bless you crazy kids this year!  Xoxo Michelle

First event of 2023…Santa Mozzarella, the team came to party!!!!!!!!! Welcome to our version of Portorosso, Italy….a fictional fisherman town inspired by the movie Luca!!!!! We created this little piazza for our little land monster, Ira!!!! Piazza Baguyo!!!! I Can. Not. Even begin to explain all the details in one post…but give me the rest of the year to try 😝😝😂😂 So I had this idea of making a ball pit into a fountain…there’s a scene in the movie where the mom Pushes and throws a bunch of kids in the fountain to see if they’re sea monsters….so I thought..OMG PERFECT…I will make the fountain …and I will Throw the children!!! Except I didn’t do the latter 😜…
Can you even believe the backdrops by Erik and crew…you guys, he added gutters to them because DETAILS!!! 🤯 To be continued…

…in the movie Luca…there’s a scene where the kids draw out their dream Vespa…so I thought…perfect!! Our kids will also draw their dream Vespa….except they’re 2 years old, so we will customize them beforehand and they’ll just paint their Vespas...like a coloring book…except with paint 😜😂. also, for this event, I wanted the bounce house to mimic the little buildings concept we built for the backdrop…so we designed some shutters and awnings …and a clothesline with the characters clothes!!! No balloons…and it stayed together the entire time!!! 🤯😂 know what else stayed together…me…yesterday at my Second root canal fiasco 🥴 I survived 👍🏻🙏🏻 and not nearly in any pain like I was following the first half…I told myself “Silenzio Bruno!!!!”…no I didn’t …but I could have 👍🏻😂.

Happy 1st of March!!!! In order to stay super relevant, today I was like…let’s go back to a party we did like six months ago!!!!! 🤌🏻👌🏻😂😂😂 we turned the birthday girl into a ballet vampire, had drinks at the “ballet bar” (get it!? 😜🫢), watched kids dance around in bat wings 🤷🏻‍♀️…it was a good time!!!!!! The amount of customizations we did for this event! 🤌🏻🦇🩰 currently, my whole little team has been feeling pretty “batty” prepping for another one coming up!! I’ll probably share this one in 2024 some time 💯🧐🤔🤔😂

The most Colossal backdrop that ever was!!!!! 🤯💗🤌🏻… Before you ask, yes…we only do Italy themed parties now 🫢😂😂😂 but come on…when the baby’s name is actually ROME!!!!!! enter Rome’s Rome!!!! This. party.  You guys…let’s just take a moment for this build by Erik and crew …the details!!!!!!! …Also those 4ft floral letters..ALL real hydrangeas!!! …took an entire Roman army to hang!!! ….today I am praising God for seeing us through this event…and for holding off pouring rain for the perfect amount of time for our party…it was misty, but not raining 😜🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 juuust enough to keep all the florals magical with water droplets…but not enough to bust out the plastic ponchos 👌🏻😝😂 Happy Birthday beautiful Rome!!!!
